00:11:45.460 --> 00:11:52.460
So who out there has, I know Bruce, you said you've done it some, anyone else done any co-authoring or considered it and why, why not?

00:11:52.460 --> 00:11:56.060
I have only co-authored books at this point in time.

00:11:56.060 --> 00:11:56.680
So.

00:11:56.680 --> 00:12:00.920
Oh, how interesting. How was your experience? So why did you go down that path?

00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:15.380
The initial book that I wrote with Jackie Kazel, she actually was writing it on her own first and then reached out to me because, yeah, the deadline, you know, she wanted to reach deadlines and two heads are better than one sometimes for that.

00:12:15.620 --> 00:12:31.020
And I think that if you're not really organized about exactly what is expected, I mean, it's the same thing as like, for example, if you were building a project with a friend on, on the side, let's say you're moonlighting or something.

00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:36.440
You're usually doing it with someone, you know, or perhaps somebody who knows somebody who you know.

00:12:36.440 --> 00:12:38.780
So there's some element of personal connection.

00:12:38.780 --> 00:12:50.720
You need to be really clear about, you know, deadlines, who's doing what, make sure it's absolutely clear and that you have some knowledge sharing in terms of who's going to cover what parts in what sequential order.

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:56.100
And this is extremely hard to do, even with bright folks by your side.

00:12:56.100 --> 00:13:11.060
But, yeah, I would say organization and really trying to use something as if you would almost do an issue tracker to really say, OK, are you going to be doing the introduction to generators here or should I do it in a later chapter and so forth?

00:13:11.060 --> 00:13:15.300
Yeah, I use an organic process, which is much harder.

00:13:15.800 --> 00:13:28.160
I guess it's not harder if it's working, but I mean, it's interesting because I see this division between when people talk about book authoring and there's the OK, you have to have a lot of structure.

00:13:28.160 --> 00:13:34.260
