Yeah, exactly.

00:42:10.940 --> 00:42:26.020
Well, when you, so when you go to journalism school or for those of you that might have had writing degrees, you kind of learn to separate writing from the type of writing that most people think and experiment with.

00:42:26.020 --> 00:42:30.620
So, like this whole concept of, like, you have to be in the mood to write and this, that.

00:42:30.620 --> 00:42:35.360
Like, if it's your job, you just can't just be like, oh, editor, I don't really feel like writing today.

00:42:35.360 --> 00:42:36.920
I think I'll go home.

00:42:37.180 --> 00:42:39.740
So, you kind of have to produce.

00:42:39.740 --> 00:42:45.380
So, I compare it to some days, like, you don't want to write code, but you need to write a few lines at least.

00:42:45.380 --> 00:42:51.680
